http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Tue 9 Apr 2019
Source: OIE, WAHIS (World Animal Health Information System), weekly disease information 2019; 32(15) [edited]
http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=30097


Newcastle disease [NCD], Cambodia
---------------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 9 Apr 2019 from Dr Sen Sovann, Director General, Ministry of Agriculture, Forestry and Fisheries, General Directorate of Animal Health and Production (GDAHP), Phnom Penh, Cambodia

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 3 Apr 2019
Date of confirmation of the event: 4 Apr 2019
Report date: 9 Apr 2019
Date submitted to OIE: 9 Apr 2019
Reason for notification: recurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 10 Jul 2018
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: Newcastle disease virus
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory basic
This event pertains to the whole country.

New outbreaks
Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak location: Tropang Russey Village, Chhor Yo, Chamkar Leu, Kg. Cham [Kampong Cham]
Date of start of the outbreak: 3 Apr 2019
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: backyard
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Birds / 57 / 23 / 23 / 0 / 34
Affected population: Newcastle virus was detected in backyard chickens.

Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed in percentages], expressed as percentages]
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Birds / 40.35 / 40.35 / 100 / 100
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: Unknown or inconclusive

Control measures
Measures applied: movement control inside the country; surveillance outside containment and/or protection zone; surveillance within containment and/or protection zone; official disposal of carcasses, by-products, and waste; zoning; disinfection; slaughter; vaccination permitted (if a vaccine exists); no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
National Animal Health and Production Research Institute (NAHPRI) (national laboratory) / Birds / real-time PCR / 4 Apr 2019 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map at the source URL above.]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Cambodia has previously reported Newcastle disease, most recently in July 2018, in Kampong Cham province (where the current outbreak is located). For more details of this previous outbreak see section 3 of Cambodia's OIE annual report at https://tinyurl.com/yxgv7fok. - Mod.CRD

